Academic activities were set to resume last Monday, but classes were disrupted by protesting students. JOHANNESBURG - The Tshwane University of Technology (TUT) says it is monitoring the situation at its Soshanguve campus following disruptions of classes this week.Academic activities were set to resume last Monday, but classes were disrupted by protesting students.The institution has deployed additional security at the campus to ensure the safety of students, staff and property, but there have been continued clashes with protesting students.TUT s Willa de Ruyter says: At all TUT s campuses, except for the Soshanguve campus, things are continuing normally. We are investigating the matter because it s not clear what renewed disruptions are about, since the agreement that activities would continue and they would allow students to complete the academic year. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)